#Set up a new set of parameters for CAMB
pars = camb.CAMBparams()

#This function sets up CosmoMC-like settings, with one massive neutrino and helium set using BBN consistency
pars.set_cosmology(H0=100.*common_settings['h'], 
                   ombh2=common_settings['omega_b'], 
                   omch2=common_settings['omega_cdm'], 
                   mnu=0., 
                   omk=0, 
                   tau=common_settings['tau_reio'],
                   TCMB=T_cmb,
                   YHe = YHe,
                   nnu=3.046,
                   num_massive_neutrinos=1)

pars.InitPower.set_params(As=common_settings['A_s'], 
                          ns=common_settings['n_s'], 
                          r=0)


pars.set_matter_power(redshifts=[0.], kmax=10., k_per_logint=130, nonlinear=True, accurate_massive_neutrino_transfers=True)



pars.NonLinear = model.NonLinear_both
pars.NonLinearModel.set_params('mead2016', HMCode_A_baryon = 3.13, HMCode_eta_baryon = 0.603)

pars.set_for_lmax(l_max_scalars, lens_potential_accuracy=8, lens_margin=2050)
pars.set_accuracy(AccuracyBoost=2.0, lSampleBoost=2.0, lAccuracyBoost=2.0,
DoLateRadTruncation=False);
print(pars)

start = time.time()
results = camb.get_results(pars)

print('Derived parameter dictionary: %s'%results.get_derived_params())
#get dictionary of CAMB power spectra
powers =results.get_cmb_power_spectra(pars, CMB_unit='muK')
for name in powers: print(name)

results.calc_power_spectra(pars)
kh_nonlin, z_nonlin, pk_nonlin = results.get_nonlinear_matter_power_spectrum(params=pars)
kh_lin, z_lin, pk_lin = results.get_linear_matter_power_spectrum(params=pars)

totCL=powers['total']
unlensedCL=powers['unlensed_scalar']

end = time.time()
seconds = end - start

print ('Time elapsed:'+strftime("%H:%M:%S", gmtime(seconds)))

M = Class()
M.set(common_settings)
M.set({'output':'tCl,pCl,lCl,mPk',
       'modes':'s',
       'lensing':'yes',
       'l_max_scalars':l_max_scalars,


       'non linear': 'hmcode',
       'eta_0' :  0.603,
       'c_min' : 3.13,
       'N_ur' : 3.046,
       
       
       'accurate_lensing': 1, #necessary to get accurate high ell lensed
       
       'k_max_tau0_over_l_max':15., #necessary to get accurate high ell lensed
       'perturb_sampling_stepsize' : 0.05, #necessary to get accurate high ell lensed
      })

start = time.time()
M.compute()

cl_unlensed_class = M.raw_cl(l_max_scalars)
cl_tot_class = M.lensed_cl(l_max_scalars)
end = time.time()
seconds = end - start
print ('Time elapsed:'+strftime("%H:%M:%S", gmtime(seconds)))

Conclusions¶

Agreement at 0.5% level for TT up to l=9000

for TE the agreement is very good, but degrad after l=4000 to 1% level

for EE the agreement is better than 0.5% level down to l=10000

For PP the agreement is better than 0.2% level all the way to l=10000

Only 3 precision parameters are needed to get high accuracy results for all these spectra, namely:
'accurate_lensing': 1,
'k_max_tau0_over_l_max':15.,
'perturb_sampling_stepsize' : 0.05,
